tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE image_processing_jobs (
  job_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  job_name VARCHAR(255),
  status VARCHAR(50),
  result JSONB,
  started_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  finished_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

CREATE TABLE image_processing_jobs (
    job_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    image_url VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    job_status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    result JSON
);

CREATE TABLE image_processing_results (
    result_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    job_id INT NOT NULL,
    result_data JSON,
    result_status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    result_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE job_history (
    history_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    job_id INT REFERENCES image_jobs(job_id),
    start_time TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMPTZ,
    status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ImageResults (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    job_id UUID NOT NULL,
    result_url VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    result_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    result_data JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (job_id) REFERENCES ImageJobs(job_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ProcessingLogs (
    log_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    job_id UUID NOT NULL,
    log_message TEXT NOT NULL,
    log_level VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (job_id) REFERENCES ImageJobs(job_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ReportHistory (
    report_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    report_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    pipeline_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    execution_date DATE NOT NULL,
    details JSONB,
    FOREIGN KEY (pipeline_status) REFERENCES PipelineStatus(pipeline_status)
);
